Main idea behind messages:
1. Service A → sends message → Broker → Service B consumes
2. Distributed BlockingQueue on steroids 

Concepts

.Queue -> Producer populates queue -> Queue post message to Consumers
.Topic -> Consumers can subscribe to topics; Each receiver gets a copy of the message
.Consumer -> Consumes the message; Responsable for processing and ACKNOWLEDGE the completition 

Message systems:

RabbitMQ - Queue based
- Broker PUSHES the messages 
- After the message is consumed it is GONE
* Services process and remove messages

Kafka - Log based
- Pull based = Consumers read at their own pace
- Allow to replay events
- Streams can be replayed and analyzed
* Services: Read independently | Can replay history | Scale separately

